Question 2¶

What is are the most commonly used stations for each city?

In [199]:
#started with a function to find the most common station for each city
#create a function to find the most common value in a column
findMcommon=function(val=0){
    #create a table of values
    a <- table(val)
    #sort that table
    b <-sort(a)
    #find the last value in the sorted table
    c <-b[length(b)]
    #return that value
    return(c)
}
In [200]:
tableOfTopStations=function(val=0, name="",type=""){
    #create a table of values
    a <- table(val)
    b <-sort(a)
    if (length(b) >=10){
        c <-data.frame ( Station.Name = c(rownames(b)[length(b)],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-1],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-2],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-3],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-4]),
                  Number.Of.Users = c(b[length(b)],
                                      b[(length(b)-1)],
                                      b[(length(b)-2)],
                                      b[(length(b)-3)],
                                      b[(length(b)-4)]),
                  Originating.From = c(name,name,name,name,name),
                  Data.Type = c(type,type,type,type,type)
                  )
    } else {
        return(0)
    }
    return(c)
}

In [229]:
tableVarTopStations=function(val=0, name="",type="",num=5){
    #create a table of values
    a <- table(val)
    b <-sort(a)
    count=0
    while (count <num){
        c <-data.frame ( Station.Name = c(rownames(b)[length(b)],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-1],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-2],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-3],
                                         rownames(b)[length(b)-4]),
                  Number.Of.Users = c(b[length(b)],
                                      b[(length(b)-1)],
                                      b[(length(b)-2)],
                                      b[(length(b)-3)],
                                      b[(length(b)-4)]),
                  Originating.From = c(name,name,name,name,name),
                  Data.Type = c(type,type,type,type,type)
                  )
        count=count+1
    }
    return(c)
}

getweekdaydf = function(val=0, name="") {
   z<-weekdays(as.Date(val$Start.Time)) 
   k<-table(z)
   weekdaydf<-as.data.frame(k)
   colnames(weekdaydf)<-c("Day","Number.Of.Start")
   weekdaydf['City']<-c(name,name,name,name,name,name,name)
   return(weekdaydf)
}
